name: Logan County Health
tweet: Naloxone has been used safely by emergency medical professionals for more than 40 years, and has only one critical function: to reverse the effects of opioids in order to prevent overdose death. Naloxone has no potential for abuse.

name: Logan County Health
tweet: Naloxone is a medication that can reverse an overdose caused by an opioid drug (like prescription pain medications or heroin).  When administered during an overdose, Naloxone blocks the effects of opioids on the brain and quickly restores breathing.  https://t.co/vKugbWV4to
